The genus Alycaeus Baird, 1850, is separated into three subgenera - Alycaeus Baird, 1850, Pincerna Preston, 1907, and Stomacosmethis Bollinger, 1918 ( Egorov 2013 ). However, all of these subgenera (including Pincerna (see
Pall-Gergely 2017
)) remain inadequately defined as no clear diagnostic characters have ever been identified ( Godwin-Austen 1889 ) and hence will require extensive revision, a task that is beyond the scope of this study and will instead be treated in later studies (B. Pall-Gergely , pers. comm.). Thus, we do not provide a diagnosis for the genus Alycaeus here pending a revision of the Alycaeidae and resolution of diagnostic characters useful for supraspecific groups. Instead, consistent with our study scope, we will only provide a description of characters relevant to Peninsular Malaysian Alycaeus species.
